52.4	American_Indian_Movement	American Indian Movement	The organization was formed to address various issues concerning the Native American urban community in Minneapolis, including poverty, housing, treaty issues, and police harassment. From its beginnings in Minnesota, AIM soon attracted members from across the United States (and Canada). It participated in the Rainbow Coalition organized by the civil rights activist Fred Hampton. Charles Deegan Sr. was involved with the AIM Patrol.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Flag_of_the_American_Indian_Movement.svg/300px-Flag_of_the_American_Indian_Movement.svg.png
